32
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:57,900
Rym: Essentially, when someone like Jack Thompson or Sony is so stupid, and they do stupid things in the news all the time, you can't report on them every time they do something stupid anymore, because that's just, well, stupid.

33
00:01:58,922 --> 00:02:01,799
Rym: So what you do is you report on the first stupid thing they do.

34
00:02:02,780 --> 00:02:13,879
Rym: If they do something else stupid, and they keep doing stupid things, you can't talk about it or say anything on the air or write a comment about it, unless the thing they just did tops everything else they've done.

35
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:18,710
Scott: Well, occasionally, I mean, someone does one stupid thing in their life.

36
00:02:18,730 --> 00:02:19,896
Scott: You say, "That guy did a stupid

37
00:02:19,917 --> 00:02:20,118
